cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.CV 

This paper is about memristive neural networks (MNNs) and their hardware implementation. The paper discusses the comparison between STDP based and non-STDP based MNNs in terms of hardware performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely categories include cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.EM (Electromagnetics), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper discusses pattern recognition as one of the applications of MNNs.
